<p> Given a positive integer <i>n</i>, find the least number of perfect
    square numbers (for example, <code>1, 4, 9, 16,
        ...</code>) which sum to <i>n</i>.
</p>
<p> For example, given <i>n</i> =
    <code>12</code>, return <code>3</code> because <code>12 = 4 + 4 + 4</code>;
    given
    <i>n</i> = <code>13</code>, return <code>2</code> because
    <code>13 = 4 + 9</code>.
</p>
